.TH "doc_erase" 9 "doc_erase" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
doc_erase \- Erase a portion of the chip
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" doc_erase
.BI "(struct mtd_info *mtd "  ","
.BI "struct erase_info *info "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mtd" 12
the device
.IP "info" 12
the erase info
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Erase a bunch of contiguous blocks, by pairs, as a "mtd" page of 1024 is
split into 2 pages of 512 bytes on 2 contiguous blocks.

Returns 0 if erase successful, -EINVAL if addressing error, -EIO if erase
issue
